To set up the frontend for TrueJustice using React.js, follow these steps:

1. Prerequisites:
Ensure Node.js and npm are installed. Download them from Node.js.
Install Git for version control.
Choose a code editor like VS Code.
2. Initialize the Project:
Create a new React app:

bash
Copy code
npx create-react-app truejustice-frontend
cd truejustice-frontend

Clean up the default project structure: Remove unnecessary files:

Delete src/logo.svg, src/App.css, and src/reportWebVitals.js.
Edit src/App.js to remove boilerplate content.

3. Install Required Packages:
Run the following commands to install the necessary libraries:

Core Libraries:

bash
Copy code
npm install react-router-dom axios

State Management:
bash
Copy code
npm install @reduxjs/toolkit react-redux

Styling:
Choose one:

Material-UI:

bash
Copy code
npm install @mui/material @emotion/react @emotion/styled

Tailwind CSS:

bash
Copy code
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer

npx tailwindcss init
Add Tailwind to src/index.css:

css
Copy code
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

Form Management and Validation:

bash
Copy code
npm install formik yup

Notifications:
bash
Copy code
npm install react-toastify

File Upload:
bash
Copy code
npm install react-dropzone

Others:
bash
Copy code
npm install moment react-icons
